  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nCast\r\n\r\n### Describe the feature you would like\r\n\r\nRight now `cast interface` only works on abi's from etherscan or abi files. \r\n`cast interface \"./out/Contract.sol/Contract.json\"` will give an error.\r\n\r\n It would be nice if it could also generate interfaces from the forge build artifacts (`out/Contract.sol/Contract.json`), where we already have the abi for the compiled contracts. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional context\r\n\r\nCan just use the abi from artifact file. \r\nArtifact file: \r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/22870103/165692321-7f08ba66-fcfd-4c97-93b0-e386c24eccf1.png)\r\n\r\n\r\nAfter a quick look at the code, If I understand correctly we are deserializing to a `Abi` type only, so attempting to deserialize to a type consistent with artifacts in case the first attempt fails would solve the issue.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/14ee6c67921e942f978b3da80f4b6049612ee64a/cast/src/lib.rs#L664-L675\r\n\r\nwdyt @onbjerg , @mattsse , @odyslam, is it worth adding? ",
